(1) An inspector may, at any time after informing the occupier or, if the occupier is not readily available, a foreman or other responsible person in the factory, take for analysis sufficient samples of any material or substance used or intended to be used in a factory, being a material or substance in respect of which he suspects a contravention of any regulation made under section seventy-four, or which he thinks is likely or may prove on analysis to be likely to cause bodily injury to the persons employed.
